 star to the extent that a normal wind ram pressure balance\ndoes not occur at any orbital phase, potentially leading to a sustained\ncollapse of the WCR onto the O star. Radiative braking may then play a\nsignificant r\\^{o}le for the WCR dynamics and resulting X-ray emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 05:38:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-27"}
